ApproxsimClient.map.graph
Class ProcessVariableXYGraph

java.lang.Object
  java.awt.Component
      java.awt.Container
          javax.swing.JComponent
              javax.swing.JPanel
                  ApproxsimClient.map.graph.ProcessVariableXYGraph
All Implemented Interfaces:
ImageObserver, MenuContainer, Serializable, EventListener, Accessible, ApproxsimEventListener
public class ProcessVariableXYGraph
extends JPanel
implements ApproxsimEventListener

This is implementation of a graph for a process variable over a time interval. One or all factions can be displayed in the same graph. The used scale can be linear or logarithmic.

ProcessVariableXYGraph

public ProcessVariableXYGraph(Timeline timeline,
                              RegionData regionData,
                              ProcessVariableDescription processVariable,
                              String[] factions,
                              Color[] factionColors,
                              String regionId)
Creates a graph for one or all factions of a process variable.

Parameters:
timeline - the reference to the timeline.
regionData - values of the sctual process variable and factionn(s).
processVariable - actual process variable for the graph.
factions - actual factions for the graph.
factionColors - colors used to visualze the different factions.
regionId - actual region.
